{"type":"e1f12c03-f736-4e0a-9847-a85100903581","value":{"en_US":"Performance requirements are important to be specified, ideally for all functions, or at least for essential functions. We allow specifying them separately from the functional requirements, because in UI intensive applications many functional requirement are grouped together into categories, and an overall performance requirement is given for all of them separately. For example: all get operations (display operations) have to take < 1sec in six sigma cases, or all write operations (save, update, add new element, etc) should take < 3sec in 6-sigma cases and so on. "},"name":"New Version","uuid":"5a544419-ab89-4586-8842-0c2073892ad9-4d31bf51-4ece-4ec9-a6cc-fc7d3585c1fa"}